Results from COVID-19 tests done on 24 July 2020  – 14 new COVID-19 cases confirmed. The cumulative total confirmed cases of Ugandans are now 1,103. – 5 truck drivers: 2 arrived via Malaba, 2 via Padea and 1 via Ngomoromo Points of Entry – 4 returnees who were under quarantine – 1 from South Sudan – 1 from Kenya – 2 from Dubai, UAE – 3 alerts – 1 alert from Kampala – 1 alert from Wakiso – 1 alert from Arua – 2 Contacts who were under quarantine – 1 contact from Namisindwa – 1 contact from Lira – 19 foreign truck drivers tested positive for COVID-19 at border points and their entry into the country was not permitted. – Ugandan Recoveries: 982 – Samples from Points of Entry tested today: 1,817 – Samples from alerts and contacts: 671 – Total samples tested today: 2,488 Distributed by APO Group on behalf of Ministry of Health – Republic of Uganda. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .